g.text: Light intensity outside the hive is a key factor influencing
bee activity. Bees rely on sunlight to determine the best
times for foraging, with their activity peaking during bright,
warm hours of the day. On cloudy days or in low light
conditions, foraging decreases as bees prefer stable and
well-lit environments for navigation. Seasonal changes in
light intensity also signal shifts in behavior, with shorter days
prompting bees to prepare for winter. Monitoring light
